      <hedline>
        <hl1>Throwing the Book At Former Gov. Whitman</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carol Karam letter on January 9 article on former New Jersey Gov Christie Whitman</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I only have one thing to say regarding Christie Whitman (''Belatedly, Whitman Comes Out Swinging,'' Jan. 9): too little, too late. Even though I voted for her, I believe that Ms. Whitman sold the state down the river, then went and did the same thing to the country.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I only have one thing to say regarding Christie Whitman (''Belatedly, Whitman Comes Out Swinging,'' Jan. 9): too little, too late. Even though I voted for her, I believe that Ms. Whitman sold the state down the river, then went and did the same thing to the country.</p>
        <p>Ms. Whitman left the state in financial trouble and the Motor Vehicle Commission in a shambles. Then, at the federal Environmental Protection Agency, she kept silent as the Bush administration pooh-poohed the idea of global warming. And now, her criticism of the administration comes in her new book only after the November election.</p>
        <p>Her decision not to make waves and to walk away with her political reputation intact was self-serving and cowardly. A ''profile in courage'' she ain't.</p>
        <p>Carol Karam  Morganville</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
